  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "Consonance is the repetition of consonant sounds in nearby words, particularly in their final positions, without matching vowel sounds: *boat/night*, *milk/talk*, *stopped/wept*. It is the consonantal counterpart of [assonance](./assonance.md) and, like assonance, operates as a subtler alternative to full [rhyme](./rhyme.md).",
